    "body": "@zcbenz I have filed the bug report to Chromium's side, but anyways after some testings, I have managed to figure out the simplest steps to reproduce the problem. I suppose these information may be useful to you.\n\n1) Open an Electron (Chromium 50+) window in transparent mode.\n\n2) Open a page with some elements that contain the \"title\" attribute.\n\n3) Resize the window after page load (using something like window.resizeBy(640,480)).\n\n4) Move the cursor around the page so that those tooltips are shown. At certain point, the GPU usage will suddenly rise noticeably.\n\nAttached is a simple app that can reproduce the problem.\n[app.zip](https://github.com/electron/electron/files/321000/app.zip)\n"
